5:
...So, yeah. I'd love to reward the
hard work, but nothing's changed
with Orgus.
8:
Things are still going all right. Maybe
it's for the best if I just let things be
for a while.
12:
...I see.
Sorry about that. I owe you one.
16:
Given our history, hearing you thank
me is a strange experience. By the
way... Have you noticed yet?
20: Heh-heh... I've found you, Sir Vyron!
25:
Well? Aren't you going to tell her
about the sword of Solon, or
something?
29:
You're probably better with one-hit
kills than I am. But no blade stands a
chance against a monster like her.
36:
He ran away again! Ohh...The
thoughtlessness of using a smoke
screen in a place like this!
41:
Sorry about this, little Demon Blade.
You even waited for us to finish our
chat.
45: Zekhel, Captain of the Guild Knights.
48:
I have heard you are the very best
combatant Palpebra has to offer.
...What say you to a duel?
52:
No way, come on. Think of the
diplomatic implications of what
you're asking for.
56: I won't take no for an answer!
72:
Somebody's sulking... You got your
duel, didn't you? Did you lose?
76:
I did NOT lose!
...Though I will admit the first strike
was very close...
80:
But he was so sluggish after that.
And he kept saying strange things
and being evasive...
85:
All right, I give up, I give up. This old
man's body can't take any more of
this, okay?
94:
Captain. It's not fair to try to walk out
at this stage.
99:
Fair? Grown-ups aren't fair. Besides,
this little Demon Blade only needs
one hit.
105:
No. If we get the chance to dance
with our blades, I would be happy to
spend all day doing this!
109:
...You sure you've got enough time
for us fuddy-duddies? Isn't there
someone else you'd rather be with
right now?
124:
Wh-what?! What does Alk have to
do with this?
128:
Come on, Shirley. You know what I'm
talking about. Alk's... pretty popular,
you know.
136:
I've heard that Alk's already received
multiple confessions from others.
149:
N-no it doesn't! It's just... Sir Alk is
much like my brother, Ciel...
156:
Hey, as his actual sister, how does
this make you feel?
161:
M-my apologies, Lady Nao. I didn't
mean to suggest that I had a
relationship to your brother similar
to yours...
166:
Oh, that's fine. I'd be happy to call
you a sister!
170:
I've liked you since the very
beginning, Celtie!
179:
Right, Shibuya. They have crazy
Halloweens, right? That should be
perfect, then.
186:
H-here's my costume... What do you
think?
192:
CUUUTE! So cute!
But, like... it's... Wow, right?
196:
This is what actual vampires are like,
though. Right, actual vampire?
202:
That's right! Each element was
hand-picked, after all! I think she
looks perfect!
207:
It's important to be sensitive to other
cultures and customs... But I worry
what Lady Stella might think.
215: P-please, get out of the waaay!
219: Fear not. I didn't draw blood.
241:
To become steel... To become the
blade!
250:
Ahh... That was a cryptic artifact... An
extremely powerful one with
telepathic abilities...
254:
B-but! As long as there aren't any
residual thoughts for the device to
resonate with, it should be fine...
259:
Oh... That outfit. I made it using
clothes left behind by a real
vampire... Is that okay?
267:
...So the Demon Blade's now a
vampire, too?
277:
...Ah, it's so boring. Just one stroke,
and everybody runs away...
280:
Weak. I cannot become steel
through the help of the weak.
290:
My reason... The light shining from
your eyes...
293:
I want to know the true form of my
feelings!
298:
Looks like we're gonna wrap up this
year's Halloween real smoothly.
